full_text: In this demo, I will cover the policy tools for an enforced policy. In the summary screen, there is a view of the contents of the policy file summarized on one screen. The screen also includes information regarding current activities, and policy transactions in progress. In the billing screen, there is a view of the overall balance and balances for individual policy periods. You can also view the payment schedule. The contacts screen displays contacts that have a role on the policy. This screen lists the contents of the policy. the users that interact with the policy by the role that they perform on the policy. The screen also shows the assigned group that the user belongs to. You can add or remove participants. For existing roles, you can change the user who performs that role. Search and view any attached documents related to the policy transaction or policy. Search and view any attached documents related to the policy transaction or policy. View summary information about all policy transactions that have occurred on the policy. The listing includes policy transactions that have modified the policy and policy transactions that are in progress, withdrawn, not taken, or non-renewed. You can also compare policy transactions. View any issues that may affect the policy. This section includes underwriting referral reasons, underwriting issues, claims, prior policies, or prior losses. You can also add, close, or reopen underwriting referral reasons. Search and view historical events that pertain to the policy. You can filter history events. The financial transactions tool is an unsupported internal tool reserved for development environments. Users with the internal tools permission are able to access this item.
